        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(voice-call): avoid OpenAI realtime double greeting",
        "body": "Fixes #85846\n\n## Summary\n\n- Keep OpenAI outbound queued initial greetings on the active explicit ready-trigger path so the provider still sends `conversation.item.create` followed by `response.create` after `session.updated`.\n- Suppress OpenAI Realtime server-VAD auto responses while a manual response is being created, then restore the original auto-response behavior on `response.done`, `response.cancelled`, and response error paths.\n- Preserve base realtime session instructions instead of moving the queued greeting into `session.update` instructions, addressing the lost-initial-response risk called out in review.\n- Keep non-OpenAI realtime providers on the existing explicit on-ready initial greeting path.\n- No config surface or plugin API surface changed.\n\n## Behavior proof\n\nThe updated focused regressions now cover the OpenAI outbound queued-greeting split and ClawSweeper's one-response-source concern:\n\n- `createBridge(...).instructions` remains the base session instructions (`\"Be helpful.\"`), so the initial greeting is not passively parked in `session.update`.\n- `onReady()` calls `triggerGreeting()` exactly once with the full queued first-turn instruction.\n- The OpenAI provider regression proves `triggerGreeting()` sends one `conversation.item.create`, temporarily updates turn detection to `create_response:false`, sends one `response.create`, then restores `create_response:true` after the manual response finishes.\n- A response-error regression proves the temporary suppression is restored if OpenAI rejects the manual response request.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 2 files, 71 tests passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts` -> 0 warnings, 0 errors\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `codex review --base origin/main` -> no actionable correctness issues found\n\nSigned head: `825a3bcff6554c745eda5ce2a0ef3e3642af47e8`.\n\nKnown proof gap: no live Twilio/OpenAI outbound call was run in this environment.",
